instName: ﻿Church of St. Mary of the Plains
﻿Church of St. Mary of the Plains

instNote: ﻿Besides the usual branches of a solid English education, the modern languages, vocal and instrumental music, drawing, and painting are taught. Terms for board and tuition are $300 per annum. A select day-school is attached to the institution.

persNote: ﻿The substantial and ornamental branches of education are taught under the direction of Mother Beatrice, Prioress

instNote: ﻿The boys' schools are under the direction of the pastors, assisted by secular teachers. The girls' school is under the charge of the Sister of Mercy
